GPG - Create key:
-----------------

1. gpg --full-generate-key
2. Select (1) RSA and RSA
3. Finish setup
4. Ensure gpg daemon is running




Pass - Configure:
-----------------
1. pass init <my-email>

2. Add the following passwords:
   pass insert oauth/google/client_id
   pass insert oauth/google/client_secret
   pass insert oauth/microsoft/client_id
   pass insert oauth/microsoft/client_secret

3. Verify (e.g):
   pass oauth/microsoft/client_id




Gmail
-----------------
1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
2. Create credentials / OAuth client ID / Application type desktop
3. Add email as test account (maybe a better way?)


Outlook
-----------------
1. Go to azure app registrations and create one

2. Add the permissions bellow:
   IMAP.AccessAsUser.All
   Mail.ReadWrite
   Mail.ReadWrite.Shared
   Mail.Send
   Mail.Send.Shared
   offline_access
   SMTP.Send
   User.Read

3. click Grant admin consent for ***





Oama
-----------
* oama authorize google <email>
* oama authorize microsoft <email>




isync
-----------
1. Ensure ~/.mail/gmail & ~/.mail/nablesolutions exist
2. mbsync -a



notmuch
-----------
1. Index emails by running:
   notmuch new
